      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For high-level boardrooms, the standard is always classic, conservative tailoring. Men should opt for dark, well-fitted suits—navy or charcoal are safest—paired with a crisp, light-colored shirt and a subtle tie. Women should favor impeccably tailored suits or professional dresses in muted tones, ensuring everything fits perfectly to project competence. Ultimately, looking authoritative means looking polished, which often means adhering to traditional, understated elegance.",
